gui.redbook.title: Book Title:
gui.redbook.description.p1: The redstone book is used in combination with the bookcase to emit a redstone signal. When placed on the bookcase a redstone signal will be emitted from all sides except the front. The strength of the signal is based on what slot on the bookcase the book occupies.
gui.redbook.description.p2: The bookcase has 16 slots, slot 1 being the top left slot and slot 16 being the bottom right. If the redstone book is placed in slot 1, the bookcase will emit no redstone signal. If the redstone book is placed in slot 2 the bookcase will emit redstone with a strength of 1. Each slot after that increases the strength by 1, all the way to slot 16 which emits a full redstone strength of 15.
gui.sign.tooltip1: Click a box or press tab to select an editing panel. Tab will cycle panels.
gui.sign.tooltip2: Click the box above to select slot 1 editing options panel. Edit scale, position, and rotation.
gui.sign.tooltip3: Click the box above to select the text editing options. Edit scale and add vanilla style formating.
gui.sign.tooltip4: Click the box above to select slot 2 for editing options. Edit scale, position, and rotation.
gui.sign.tooltip6: Adjust block rotation. Blocks can face to the left, center, or right. Items can only face left or right.
gui.sign.tooltip7: Adjust block position. Position can also be adjusted with the arrow keys or the WASD keys.
gui.sign.tooltip8: Enter one of the following numbers/ letters after the formatting symbol:
gui.sign.tooltip9: Click the button or press the 'alt' key to add a formatting symbol to the selected line.
